, "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This code fails\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::ops::Deref;\r\n\r\npub struct Foo {}\r\n\r\npub trait Bar {\r\n    fn t(&self) -> &Foo;\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<B: Bar + ?Sized, R: Deref<Target = B>> Bar for R {\r\n    fn t<'a>(&'a self) -> &'a Foo {\r\n        self.deref().t()\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nShortened error message:\r\n```\r\nerror[E0309]: the parameter type `B` may not live long enough\r\n   |      -- help: consider adding an explicit lifetime bound...: `B: 'a +`\r\n```\r\nAdding such a constraint is (a) impossible and (b) already implied,\r\n\r\nReplacing `Foo` with a trait yields the same error.\r\n\r\nTested on 1.53.0 and `9c25eb7aa 2021-07-25` nightly.\r\n\r\nPossibly this is #80675.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/87486/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 1}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/87486/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}